Build A Bear Workshop : A-Bear donates 5,000 bears to Red Cross 



































0






07/20/2017 | 08:48pm CEST 


Send by mail :
Last Name :
Name :
From* :
To* :
(You can enter multiple email addresses separated by commas)
Message :
*Required fields





July 20--To help comfort children following a tornado, fire or other disaster, the American Red Cross will soon hand out 5,000 stuffed animals donated by Build-A-Bear Workshop.
Overland-based Build-A-Bear donated the stuffed animals this week to five Red Cross Disaster Field Supply Centers in St. Louis; Reno, Nev.; Carlisle, Penn., Atlanta and Dallas.
The bears and other stuffed animals will be distributed from the Red Cross' disaster action vehicles, along with  blankets, water, snacks and hygiene products, as part of the nonprofit's disaster relief operations.
In St. Louis, the Red Cross responds to an average of three fires a day, said Hannah Bruce, disaster program specialist with the American Red Cross, Eastern Missouri Region.
"A lot of times after a fire, they've lost all of their toys, and with this donation, they'll be able to give the child something to call their own," she said.
Build-A-Bear operates about 400 stores and had $364.2 million in fiscal 2016 revenue.
___
